title: Very poor customer service
text: Our son and daughter in law tried to cancel YMCA Prescott membership starting in September 2023. They canceled online first. Then by phone and finally in person.  The YMCA continued to take monthly dues through February this year.  Both our son and his wife had surgeries during this time and were unable to use the gym. This was all explained to director of YMCA.  She was unsympathetic and refused to refund the hundreds of dollars they had taken. BEWARE OF THIS ORGANIZATION.  It is extremely hard to cancel membership once you join.  DO NOT JOIN.

title: Big Mistake
text:
I had Google on my phone and computer. I did not agree with what they were doing to ether. I  removed all my information, the emails, my maps, my contacts, the Google apps, from my phone and computer. Then  I deleted all of the information that had anything to do with Google. 

It took me and several technicians to accomplish this task. Google is like a cancer; Ya don’t want it, you do EVERYTHING you can to get rid of it. You think to yourself that Google is gone off all your internet devices, then out of the blue, it shows up again. 

I contacted Google 3 times, they wanted me to pay them like $80. Plus and then they wouldn’t help me get Google off my devices. I tell them that this is their fault and; Click, Silence, they hung up on me. They are no more than a company that was built on empty promises that they will back up they’re product and services. They people whom runs these Google companies and obvious the employees that work at the same Google companies are selfish, greedy, self centered people that obviously loves to take advantage of their customers. 

Don’t Use Them. You’ll find that it would be a HUGE MISTAKE.
